    "reasoning": "To implement the Rule 90 cellular automaton, we need to follow these steps:\n1. Initialize a 512-element array to store the current state of the cells.\n2. Apply the Rule 90 update rule to each cell based on its left, center, and right neighbors.\n3. Load the initial state from the 'data' input when 'load' is asserted.\n4. Handle the boundary conditions by treating the edges as 0 (off).\n5. Update the state on each positive edge of the clock.\n6. Ensure the design matches the given module interface and avoids syntax errors.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input logic clk,\n    input logic load,\n    input logic [511:0] data,\n    output logic [511:0] q\n);\n\n    // Initialize the 512-element array with zeros\n    logic [511:0] cells;\n    initial begin\n        cells = 0;\n    end\n\n    // Function to apply Rule 90 update rule\n    function logic [511:0] apply_rule_90;\n        input logic [511:0] state;\n        logic [511:0] updated_state;\n        integer i;\n        updated_state = state;\n        for (i = 0; i < 512; i++) begin\n            updated_state[i] = state[(i-1+512)%512] ^ state[i] ^ state[(i+1)%512];\n        end\n        return updated_state;\n    endfunction\n\n    // Process to handle loading and updating\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (load) begin\n            cells = data;\n        end else begin\n            cells = apply_rule_90(cells);\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Assign the current state to the output\n    assign q = cells;\n\nendmodule"
}
